keyFacts: The document is a Bureau of Prisons transfer receipt dated August 9, 2019.
It records the transfer of three prisoners: Ronnell Booth, Javon Bussey, and Efrain Reyes from MCC New York.
All three prisoners were in the custody of the USMS/SDNY (U.S. Marshals Service, Southern District of New York) and had a status of 'PRE REMOVE'.
The document confirms all medical records, disciplinary reports, and pending paperwork for the prisoners were accounted for at the time of transfer.
This administrative document shows standard prison transfer procedures but does not directly mention Jeffrey Epstein or his case.
